        messageTypeName - name of root message to parse from binary data
        containsDelimitedMessages - data structure of root message. false = one single message, true = multiple delimited messages

      • containsDelimitedMessages

        public boolean containsDelimitedMessages()
        Get if the parsed data contains multiple delimited messages. In such a case you have to pass the message index to the most for the other functions of this class.
        Returns:
        true if the parsed data contains multiple delimited messages, false = single message (normal case)

      • getDynamicMessageList

        public java.util.ArrayList<com.google.protobuf.DynamicMessage> getDynamicMessageList()
        Get all of the messages (multiple delimited messages).
        CAUTION: if you convert the returned ArrayList to an array and make later any modification by using setFieldValue(int delimitedMessageIndex, String key, Object value) then you must convert once again the ArrayList to an array to get the updated messages.
        Returns:
        all of the messages
        See Also:
        should be true, setFieldValue(int delimitedMessageIndex, String key, Object value)
